honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class VersionInformation

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.VersionInformation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class VersionInformation
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {VR?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    BBoot Version
    CComm Controller Version
    DDownload Version
    FFirmware Version
    HHardware Controller Version
    S1-SCRSCR Version
    TBuild Timestamp
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • VersionInformation

        public VersionInformation(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

      • getBootVersion_IsPresent

        public boolean getBootVersion_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getBootVersion() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getBootVersion() may not be valid.

        Returns:
        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        getBootVersion()
